observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management:
Create an Inventory Committee with adequate number of members to be able to complete the physical inventory in three months or less, who will coordinate with the General Services Office (GSO) in the preparation of a Physical Inventory Plan (PIP) in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006 to promote the conduct of the required annual physical count of PPE, and to address the unreconciled balances between the Accounting and the General Services Office;
Require the GSO to coordinate with the Accounting Office to determine the items to be included in the RPCPPE with consideration on the capitalization threshold of ₱15,000.00, and with the Inventory Committee on the details and other relevant information to ensure the proper accomplishment of the RPCPPE;
Require the Municipal Accountant and the GSO-designate to maintain the required PPE Ledger Cards and Property Cards, respectively;
Instruct the Inventory Committee to initiate the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts in accordance to COA Circular No. 2020-006; and
Consider the manpower requirement of the Accounting and General Services Office for the preparation and maintenance of required records.

We recommended that the Management:
Collection of mobilization fee shall be for every progress billing equivalent to the percentage of the advance payment against the total contract cost until fully paid;
Deduct the retention money at 10% per progress billing;
Deduct the uncollected retention money for the projects “Construction of Reinforced Concrete Deck Girder Phase 2” and “Construction of Two (2) Storey Public Market” on the next progress billings of the contractor; and
Strictly observe the provisions of the revised IRR of the RA 9184.

Recommendations:

Submit the said lacking documentary requirements as shown in the attached schedule (Annex F);

Comply with the posting requirements provided under GPPB-TSO Advisory No. 05-2020 on the procurement projects undertaken through Emergency Procurement under the Bayanihan Act;

Require the Municipal Accountant to meticulously review and ensure completeness and propriety of the required supporting documents for all related disbursements in accordance with the applicable laws, rules and regulations.

Recommendations:

Observe the perpetual inventory method in accounting of inventories;

Prepare and maintain the required forms, subsidiary records and periodic reports, such as SLC, SC, RIS and RSMI, as prescribed in the Government Accounting Manual for LGUs;

Conduct periodic physical count of inventories to determine any necessary adjustments in the books and inventory records.
